Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 172 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 185, 3, misread. Name Nikasagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX GAB 1060?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0908)
